Hi, and welcome back to Line Sheet. Today is Rachel
=E2=80=9CRachel@puck.news=E2=80=9D Strugatz Day, and as per usual, she=E2=
=80=99s serving beauty industry intel that literally no one else can gather=
=2E This week, she=E2=80=99s got the insi=
de story of how Carolina Herrera=E2=
=80=99s Good Girl, launched in 2016, unseated Chanel=E2=80=99s Chance as th=
e top-selling fragrance in the world. (Yes, you read that right.) Up top, I=
 deliver the latest on the Saks Global layoffs, plus murmurs of changes on =
the executive side of the LVMH Fashion Group.

By the time you read this, I=E2=80=99ll be in Milan, maybe even asleep? (I =
landed just a couple of hours ago from London.) For those who were here, th=
ough, the day was jammed with shows (Diesel, Jil Sander, Fendi), and transi=
tion is the only word I can muster to summarize them. A few hours after the=
 Jil Sander models walked, parentco OTB announced that Luke and Lucie Meier=
, the brand=E2=80=99s co-creative directors, are leaving, a turn of events
that I previewed a few weeks back ( https://puck.news/simone-bellotti-leave=
