=80=99s challenging to pay within 30 days for a product that might not sell=
 for six months.<br/><br/>Finally, he emphasized that Saks Global is <em>on=
e</em> company, and there would be zero tolerance for old-school Saks versu=
s Neimans versus Bergdorf=E2=80=99s nonsense. Of course, a level of competi=
tion among coworkers is healthy and effective. But the public-facing
team, in particular, needs to show a united front in Milan and Paris in the=
