ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;">Even within the cutthroat beauty business, there is no subcategory more=
 fiercely
contested than women=E2=80=99s fragrance. Chanel, Dior, YSL Beauty, and a f=
ew others have historically dominated, cycling in and out of the top spots =
and spending lavishly to establish and defend their positions. Which is why=
 I was shocked to learn that the past year=E2=80=99s bestselling women=E2=
=80=99s fragrance franchise is not from one of the Big Three, but=E2=80=A6 =
Carolina Herrera=E2=80=99s Good Girl, the citrusy-sweet perfume that comes =
bottled in a mini stiletto heel.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-botto=
m:0px;">=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Incredibly, according to Circana c=
onsumer data, Good Girl isn=E2=80=99t just the top perfume brand in the U.S=
=2E; it was also the bestselling wom=
en=E2=80=99s fragrance <em>in the world</=
em> last year, supplanting Chanel=E2=80=99s Chance. (Valentino Donna, Dior=
=E2=80=99s Miss Dior, and Chanel=E2=80=99s Coco Mademoiselle round out the =
rest of the top five.) Yes, yes, these rankings are estimates, compiled fro=
m a number of data points, so take them with a grain of salt. But the dethr=
oning of Chanel,
long the category leader, is a huge deal.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bo=
ttom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Carolina Herr=
era=E2=80=99s momentum may not be surprising to analysts who=E2=80=99ve spe=
nt time on TikTok, which has helped propel the brand. But the real credit g=
oes to Puig, the Spanish beauty and fashion conglomerate that acquired Caro=
lina Herrera in 1995, transforming a company best known for its gala wear i=
nto one of the world=E2=80=99s biggest sellers of designer fragrances. More
recently, Puig has been at the forefront of some of beauty=E2=80=99s bigges=
t M&amp;A deals, acquiring a majority stake in Charlotte Tilbury in 2020 an=
d Byredo in 2022. Puig went public last May in the largest European offerin=
g of 2024.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">Long before the I.P.O., however, Puig =
began laying the groundwork for the upmarket consumer strategy that=E2=80=
=99s now paying dividends. The company spent the past two decades
reinventing itself from a regional mass market player to compete with LVMH,=
 L=E2=80=99Or=C3=A9al, and Coty. In 2022, Puig reached 10 percent worldwide=
 market share of =E2=80=9Cselective fragrances,=E2=80=9D a subcategory that=
 includes designer perfumes, more than tripling its market share since 2004=
=2E=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margi=
n-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"m=
argin:0;">At its earnings call tomorrow, Puig is expected to announce that =
it has surpassed 11 percent market share. =E2=80=9CA lot of Puig=E2=80=99s =
[previous] business was
in mass market, and mostly in Spain, and they stopped all of this=E2=80=93=
=E2=80=93which was profitable=E2=80=93=E2=80=93and decided to focus on frag=
rance and fashion and nothing else until they commanded 10 percent of marke=
t share in fragrance,=E2=80=9D said a person with knowledge of their trajec=
tory.</p></div>
